        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Jewellery trends often come and go, but some styles return with even more meaning. Over the last few years, vintage-inspired rings have quietly made a strong comeback. Surprisingly, it’s not just collectors or antique lovers who are driving this trend -  Gen Z buyers are embracing vintage designs more than ever. </p><p>For many younger jewellery buyers, vintage rings feel personal and expressive. They carry the charm of the past while still fitting into modern fashion. Instead of choosing overly flashy designs, many Gen Z customers prefer rings that tell a story.</p><p>At Lucira Jewelry, vintage-inspired rings combine classic detailing with modern craftsmanship. Designs like the Vintage<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/oval-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/oval-rings\"> Halo Oval Diamond Ring</a> or the Round Solitaire Vintage Engagement Ring reflect the elegance of earlier eras while still feeling wearable today.</p><p>So what exactly is behind this renewed love for vintage rings?</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qw7HLy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Appeal of Old-World Craftsmanship in a Modern World",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Appeal of Old-World Craftsmanship in a Modern World</h2>",
            "custom_id": "the-appeal",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_WfQaQ4": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/How_to_Style_a_Solitaire_Ring_for_Work_Without_Looking_Overdressed.jpg"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_JMmk6L": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>One reason vintage rings attract younger buyers is the level of detail in their designs. Older jewellery styles often featured delicate patterns, intricate settings, and thoughtful craftsmanship.</p><p>These elements create a ring that feels unique rather than mass-produced.</p><p>Take the Regency Bloom Diamond Ring for example. The design includes soft floral inspiration and subtle detailing that makes the ring feel artistic. Pieces like this remind people of jewellery from another time - when designs were created with patience and careful attention.</p><p>For many buyers today, that kind of craftsmanship feels refreshing.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
